txt.en: Instance: Daughter of Strife
'We have you now. Get them, lads!'
'Do hurry; I have something wonderful to show thee!'
'Thou didst not tell my father, did thee? Thou knowest how he worries.'
'The smiths have taught me all they know, and yet He knows so much more... come, thou must meet him!'
'I thought she handled herself quite well.'
'Do not be frightened; Antheron promised there was naught for me to fear.'
'But, who is this that thou hast brought with thee?'
'Orcs! Come, let us test our strength.'
'Thy father would forbid thee from learning more of the world outside.'
'Dost thou see? No uruk can withstand the might of the Noldor!'
'Come with me, Narmeleth!'
'For Elbereth!'
'A second assault? Come! I welcome the battle!'
'I can show thee how to make things not even the mind of FÃ«anor has imagined.'
'Narmeleth, what is this foolishness?'
'I must be on my guard... who knows how many more Orcs there could be?'
'Would thou be trapped in Mirobel forever?'
'Are you well, friend?  I lost sight of thee in the heat of the battle.'
'Come, it is not far now!'
'I already forbade thee from speaking to this... this Gift-lord, and now thou dost sneak out to meet with him?'
'See how they quake before my blade!'
'Come, Narmeleth. We shall begin thy learning immediately.'
'And father says I am not ready to fight in the wars. See how they fall before me!'
'Thou would order my daughter to defy me?'
'Maybe this was not such a wise choice...'
'Come, Narmeleth. We are returning to Mirobel at once!'
'Father, I...'
'Hold thy tongue, or I shall show it to thee!'
'I can explain, I...'
'Narmeleth, I...'
'Father, no!'
'...I love thee.'
'I am leaving with Antheron. If thou love me, thou will not stop me.'
